cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on event detection from social media, specifically Twitter.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper proposes two algorithms for event detection.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper involves analyzing and processing large amounts of text data.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is relevant as the paper uses semantic analysis via word embedding to enhance event detection.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of social media on news media and event detection.
